08/10/2009
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- The director of the European Commission (EC) Enlargement Directorate, Michael Leigh, confirmed on Wednesday (October 7th) that the EC will send experts to monitor the November 15th municipal elections in Kosovo. The EC presence in these first elections since independence was declared last year was requested by the government in July. EC personnel will "assess and report on the two rounds of the upcoming municipal elections", Leigh said in his official reply. (RTK, Kohavision, TV 21 - 07/10/09)
